article.headline: San Diego 42, Davidson 0
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Mason Mills threw three touchdown passes and rushed for a fourth score as the University of San Diego beat Davidson, 42-0, in a Pioneer Football League game on Saturday. USD's Kenny James returned the second-half kickoff 95 yards for a touchdown. He scored on a 4-yard run in the first half that ended with the Toreros (4-1, 2-0) ahead 28-0. Mills, who completed 16 of 24 passes for 191 yards in just three quarters, threw TD passes of 21 and 10 yards to brothers Nick and Sam Scudellari, respectively. Mills also found John McGough on a 38-yard TD strike and scored on a 5-yard run in the third quarter. San Diego's defense shut down Davidson quarterback Jonathan Carkhuff, who came into the game leading FCS football in passing yards (382.67) and completions (32.0) per game. Carkhuff completed finished the day 26 for 43 for 160 yards for the Wildcats (2-2, 0-1).
